- Write journal_dump program:
  - Loads in the directory listing of the journal directory
  - Reads in each file
  - Outputs a formatted text description of each record in the file
  - Optionally waits for new records to be output to the "current" file

- Make the sync timing intelligent in order to batch transactions.

- When journald is killed, sync and rotate the output file, but don't
  open a new one.
